\begin_layout Subparagraph*
Violence data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Monthly statistics on levels of ongoing violence were gathered from several
 sources.
 The number of service personnel killed per month were collected from a
 Fundación Paz y Reconciliación (PARES) report and a Defense Ministry report.
 (The PARES report cites the Defense Ministry as the source for its figures.)
 [
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Lo que hemos ganado
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

] [Ministerio de Defensa] It should be noted that these numbers may include
 casualties from a smaller ongoing conflict with the ELN; however, in other
 Defense Ministry statistics that are disaggregated by rebel group (e.g.
 number of demobilized militants), FARC's contribution is overwhelming.
 An additional statistic, the number of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

armed actions
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

offensive actions
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 of FARC per month were collected from data available from two Colombian
 conflict analysis groups.
 For 2012-2014, the source of the data was Fundación Paz y Reconciliación
 (PARES).
 For 2015-2016, data from PARES was not available and was collected instead
 from the Centro de Recursos para el Análisis de Conflictos (CERAC).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph*
Public opinion data.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Monthly public opinion data was collected from the Centro Nacional De Consultorí
a, a Colombian consultancy firm.
 Answers to the questions, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Do you have a positive or negative image of President Juan Manuel Santos?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Do you approve of the decision of President Santos to open peace talks with
 the guerrillas?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Author's translation from Spanish.
 It should be noted that the latter question is missing before September
 2012 because the peace process had not started yet!
\end_layout

\end_inset

 were recorded as approval ratings for the president and for the peace process,
 respectively.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph*
Structural breaks.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The optimal structural breaks for each sentiment/actor, using loessed values,
 were identified using Zeileis et al.'s strucchange R package.
 [Zeileis] There were no structural breaks identified in positive government
 emotion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename neg_g.eps
	width 100text%

\end_inset


\end_layout

