\begin_layout Standard
Comparing Model (1) vs.
 (2) and model (3) vs.
 (4) shows that the inclusion of covariates does little to improve fit.
 The improvement in BIC and AIC values in the two-state model over the one-state
 model demonstrates that a mixture is a better fit for the data than a single
 state.
 Focusing on the two FARC models, with and without covariates, the BIC values
 suggest that 
\begin_inset Formula $n=3$
\end_inset

 optimizes the number of latent states: although 
\begin_inset Formula $n=4$
\end_inset

 has a slightly better BIC value than 
\begin_inset Formula $n=3$
\end_inset

 in both models, the improvement is marginal and is weighed against the
 consideration that the fewest possible number of latent states should be
 chosen.
 The AIC values for the FARC models, however, as well as both the BIC and
 AIC values for the government models, favor higher order specifications.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However, these improvements in fit must be balanced against the tradeoff
 in the interpretability of results in a model with so many states (e.g.
 what is the substantive meaning of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

1/5 willingness to negotiate
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 or a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

transition for 1/5 to 2/5 hardline
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

?).
 Consequently, the following analysis will proceed with a HMM with three
 latent states, or regimes.
 The violence and public opinion covariates are not included.
 The latent states represent high, moderate, and low willingness to negotiate.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As discussed in the Methods section, the hidden Markov model estimation
 does not attach substantive labels to numbered states, nor does it order
 the states (i.e.
 by magnitude).
 For instance, state 1 may correspond with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

high,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 state 2 with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

low,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and state 3 with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

moderate.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


