\begin_layout Standard
As shown in the fit statistics at the bottom of the table, the AIC and the
 BIC identify different models as the best choice, models (4) and (2) respective
ly.
 However, the log likelihood value suggests that the reduced model, (1),
 is actually the best fit.
 In the interest of parsimony, the following analysis will utilize model
 (1).
 I also use pairwise likelihood ratio tests (see Appendix).
\end_layout

